-- Empty Tanker Ship Runs Aground Off Sicily, All Crew Reach Safety
-- B y   E l i s a   M a r t i n u z z i
-- 2012-03-10T12:58:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-10/empty-tanker-ship-runs-aground-off-sicily-all-crew-reach-safety.html
A tanker ship today ran aground off
the coast of Siracuse, Sicily, and all 19 crew members have been
brought to safety, a coast guard officer told SkyTG24
television.  A towing vessel is already on site, officer Filippo Marini
told SkyTG24. The ship hit rocks amid strong winds and heavy
seas, he said.  The Italian ship was empty at the time, newspaper  Corriere
della Sera  reported on its website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisa Martinuzzi in Milan at 
 emartinuzzi@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
